      "file": "README.md",
      "patch": "# Docr

A modern document management application.

## Overview

Docr is a web-based application for managing and organizing documents, featuring a dynamic repository system.

## Features

- Repository management
- Document organization
- Dynamic page routing
- Modern React-based interface

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Node.js
- npm or yarn

### Installation

```bash
git clone https://github.com/therealteejay25/Docr.git
cd Docr
npm install
```

### Running the Application

```bash
npm run dev
```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:3000`

## Project Structure

```
app/
  ├── repos/
  │   └── [id]/       # Dynamic repository pages
  └── ...
```

## Contributing

Contributions are welcome! Please feel free to submit a Pull Request.

## License

This project is licensed under the MIT License.

      "file": "ARCHITECTURE.md",
      "patch": "# Docr Architecture

## Overview

Docr is built using modern web technologies with a focus on dynamic routing and repository management.

## Technical Stack

- Next.js/React for frontend
- Dynamic routing for repository pages
- Modern JavaScript/TypeScript

## Key Components

### Repository Pages

Location: `app/repos/[id]/page.tsx`

Handles individual repository views with dynamic routing based on repository ID.

## Data Flow

1. User requests repository page
2. Dynamic route captures repository ID
3. Page component renders repository-specific content

## Future Considerations

- Authentication system
- Document versioning
- Search functionality
